    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That \"balanced approach\" sounds good in theory, but it feels like you're basically saying the \"tough on crime\" side is just outdated or misguided. Can't someone be both concerned about public safety and also believe in strict enforcement? It feels like you're framing one side as \"the solution\" and the other as just \"temporary\" or \"neglectful.\"",
