      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're absolutely right that strict enforcement matters for violent crimes, yet relying solely on \"tough on crime\" laws ignores that we over-criminalize minor offenses while under-investing in the schools and jobs that prevent crime. Deterrence is useful as one tool, but without simultaneously building community resilience through education and economic opportunity, we just get more prisons without lasting safety. True progress comes from recognizing that harsh penalties alone can't fix the systemic failures that breed disorder and injustice.",
